{"word":"ἄπυστος","slug":"ἄπυστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄπυστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πυνθάνομαι'><el>πυνθάνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>not heard of</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <el>ἄπυστα φωνῶν</el> speaking <i>what none can hear</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>without hearing</i> or <i>learning</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}